cdx6500PCTSDLCPortTable.name: cdx6500PCTSDLCPortTable
cdx6500PCTSDLCPortTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the SDLC Port table.

cdx6500PCTSDLCPortEntry.name: cdx6500PCTSDLCPortEntry
cdx6500PCTSDLCPortEntry.description: A row of SDLC Port configuration parameters.

cdx6500sdlcpCfgPortNum.name: cdx6500sdlcpCfgPortNum
cdx6500sdlcpCfgPortNum.description: Specifies a specific port (physical port number) in the node.

cdx6500sdlcpSubType.name: cdx6500sdlcpSubType
cdx6500sdlcpSubType.description: This is the SDLC port subtype hpad - Host PAD. tpad - Terminal PAD. newvalHpad - same functionality as 'hpad', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500sdlcpTxCoding.name: cdx6500sdlcpTxCoding
cdx6500sdlcpTxCoding.description: This is the data encoding used on the SDLC link. nrz - Non Return to Zero nrzi - Non Return to Zero Inverted newvalNrz - same functionality as 'nrz', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500sdlcpLineType.name: cdx6500sdlcpLineType
cdx6500sdlcpLineType.description: Type of line, indicates whether half duplex or full duplex signals are being generated. fdx - communications occuring in both directions simultaneously between devices. hdx - transmission occuring in both directions, but only one direction at a time. This operation is not currently supported. hdxdce - (Half Duplex DCE) This is used on the HPAD when the port is a DCE and the port is interfacing directly to a FEP. The port detects RTS go HIGH, waits RTS TO CTS DELAY ms, and raises CTS. newvalHdx - same functionality as 'hdx', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500sdlcpTxType.name: cdx6500sdlcpTxType
cdx6500sdlcpTxType.description: This is the transmission mode used on the line. tws - Two way Simultaneout. twa - Two Way Alternate used by most controllers. newvalTws - same functionality as 'tws', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500sdlcpSendSigDelay.name: cdx6500sdlcpSendSigDelay
cdx6500sdlcpSendSigDelay.description: This object is replaced by cdx6500sdlcpHPADResponseDelay. This is a configurable delay that defines the amount of time that the HPAD delays before sending a response to the HOST. The delay is specified in milliseconds.

cdx6500sdlcpClock.name: cdx6500sdlcpClock
cdx6500sdlcpClock.description: int - Internal clock source. ext - External clock source. newvalInt - same functionality as 'int', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500sdlcpClockSpeed.name: cdx6500sdlcpClockSpeed
cdx6500sdlcpClockSpeed.description: This is the speed of the port in bits per second, when using internal clocking.

cdx6500sdlcpNumControllers.name: cdx6500sdlcpNumControllers
cdx6500sdlcpNumControllers.description: This is the number of controllers (PU TYPE 1 or PU TYPE 2 devices) on the SDLC line.

cdx6500sdlcpPollTimer.name: cdx6500sdlcpPollTimer
cdx6500sdlcpPollTimer.description: Worst case delay for a slave to respond to a poll frame sent by the master, including modem turn around time, etc. Value in 10ths of second ( 30 = 3.0 seconds ).

cdx6500sdlcpPollFrequency.name: cdx6500sdlcpPollFrequency
cdx6500sdlcpPollFrequency.description: Time in milliseconds between polls when no data is exchanged.

cdx6500sdlcpTries.name: cdx6500sdlcpTries
cdx6500sdlcpTries.description: Maximum number of attempts to complete a transmission.

cdx6500sdlcpOptions.name: cdx6500sdlcpOptions
cdx6500sdlcpOptions.description: Select options on this SDLC port as follows: NONE - no option specified MARKi - port uses mark idle between frame exchanges (Required by System 36 - AS/400 series) DMs - HPAD does not send DM in response to SNRM/XID received from host. After call is accepted and TPAD responds with QUA/QXID, HPAD will send UA/XID. DISCs - TPAD sends a DISC frame when station goes down. The DISC may be retransmitted up to Tries times, if the Cluster Controller does not respond, before sending a SNRM. FFBF - TPAD sends a broadcast XID. If the number of controllers configured is equal to 1 and the associated QLLC station table option is not XIDs the TPAD will poll with a broadcast address until a secondary station response address is received.

cdx6500sdlcpPortAddress.name: cdx6500sdlcpPortAddress
cdx6500sdlcpPortAddress.description: When an SDLC port makes a call, this address is inserted into the calling address field.

cdx6500sdlcpPortOptions.name: cdx6500sdlcpPortOptions
cdx6500sdlcpPortOptions.description: Specify any of the following port control options: NONE - no option specified MB - raise Pin 22 when the port becomes disabled

cdx6500sdlcpHPADResponseDelay.name: cdx6500sdlcpHPADResponseDelay
cdx6500sdlcpHPADResponseDelay.description: This object replaces cdx6500sdlcpSendSigDelay. This is a configurable delay that defines the amount of time that the HPAD delays before sending a response to the HOST. The delay is specified in milliseconds. newvalMsec0 : same functionality as 'msec0', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500sdlcpMaxFrameSize.name: cdx6500sdlcpMaxFrameSize
cdx6500sdlcpMaxFrameSize.description: Maximum size (in bytes) of a frame, excluding the frame header and CRC.

cdx6500sdlcpRtsCtsDelay.name: cdx6500sdlcpRtsCtsDelay
cdx6500sdlcpRtsCtsDelay.description: Delay in milliseconds that the HDX DCE TPAD or the HDXDCE HPAD waits from the time it detects RTS go HIGH until the time it raises CTS. It is accurate to +/- 2 milliseconds.

cdx6500sdlcpElectricalInterfaceType.name: cdx6500sdlcpElectricalInterfaceType
cdx6500sdlcpElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

cdx6500sdlcpV24ElectricalInterfaceOption.name: cdx6500sdlcpV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500sdlcpV24ElectricalInterfaceOption.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

cdx6500sdlcpHighSpeedElectricalInterface.name: cdx6500sdlcpHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500sdlcpHighSpeedElectricalInterface.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500PPSTSDLCPortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTSDLCPortTable
cdx6500PPSTSDLCPortTable.description: All of the statistics parameters relevant to the SDLC Port table.

cdx6500PPSTSDLCPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTSDLCPortEntry
cdx6500PPSTSDLCPortEntry.description: A row of SDLC Port statistics parameters.

cdx6500sdlcpStatsPortNum.name: cdx6500sdlcpStatsPortNum
cdx6500sdlcpStatsPortNum.description: Specifies a specific port (physical port number) in the node.

cdx6500sdlcpPortStatus.name: cdx6500sdlcpPortStatus
cdx6500sdlcpPortStatus.description: Specifies the current port status. up : At least one station is responding to polls. down : None of the stattions are responding to polls. disabled : The port is disabled by the user. newvalDisabled : same functionality as 'disabled', new enumeration added for RFc1155 compatibility.

cdx6500sdlcpPortSpeed.name: cdx6500sdlcpPortSpeed
cdx6500sdlcpPortSpeed.description: The measured port speed in bits per second.

cdx6500sdlcpCharInTotal.name: cdx6500sdlcpCharInTotal
cdx6500sdlcpCharInTotal.description: Total number of characters received until now, not including all SDLC header characters.

cdx6500sdlcpCharOutTotal.name: cdx6500sdlcpCharOutTotal
cdx6500sdlcpCharOutTotal.description: Total number of characters transmitted until now, not including all SDLC header characters.

cdx6500sdlcpCharsInPerSec.name: cdx6500sdlcpCharsInPerSec
cdx6500sdlcpCharsInPerSec.description: The average number of characters received per second during the previous minute.

cdx6500sdlcpCharsOutPerSec.name: cdx6500sdlcpCharsOutPerSec
cdx6500sdlcpCharsOutPerSec.description: The average number of characters transmitted per second during the previous minute.

cdx6500sdlcpFrameInTotal.name: cdx6500sdlcpFrameInTotal
cdx6500sdlcpFrameInTotal.description: Total number of SDLC frames received until now.

cdx6500sdlcpFrameOutTotal.name: cdx6500sdlcpFrameOutTotal
cdx6500sdlcpFrameOutTotal.description: The total number of SDLC frames transmitted until now.

cdx6500sdlcpFramesInPerSec.name: cdx6500sdlcpFramesInPerSec
cdx6500sdlcpFramesInPerSec.description: The average number of frames received per second during the previous minute.

cdx6500sdlcpFramesOutPerSec.name: cdx6500sdlcpFramesOutPerSec
cdx6500sdlcpFramesOutPerSec.description: The average number of frames transmitted per second during the previous minute.

cdx6500sdlcpStateChange.name: cdx6500sdlcpStateChange
cdx6500sdlcpStateChange.description: The date and time when the link entered the current state.

cdx6500sdlcpLinkDowns.name: cdx6500sdlcpLinkDowns
cdx6500sdlcpLinkDowns.description: Total number of times link has made a transition from the UP state to the DOWN state.

cdx6500sdlcpUtilizationIn.name: cdx6500sdlcpUtilizationIn
cdx6500sdlcpUtilizationIn.description: Indicates a percentage of the link resources currently in use in the IN(from the line to the port) direction.

cdx6500sdlcpUtilizationOut.name: cdx6500sdlcpUtilizationOut
cdx6500sdlcpUtilizationOut.description: Indicates a percentage of the link resources currently in use in the OUT(from the port to the line) direction.

cdx6500sdlcpOverrunErrors.name: cdx6500sdlcpOverrunErrors
cdx6500sdlcpOverrunErrors.description: Total number of overrun errors counted by the I/O driver. Overrun errors occur when received data is lost because it cannot be processed by the CPU.

cdx6500sdlcpUnderrunErrors.name: cdx6500sdlcpUnderrunErrors
cdx6500sdlcpUnderrunErrors.description: Total number of underrun errors counted by the I/O driver. Underrun errors occur when the transmission of a frame cannot be completed because of momentary CPU overload.

cdx6500sdlcpCRCErrors.name: cdx6500sdlcpCRCErrors
cdx6500sdlcpCRCErrors.description: Total number of CRC errors counted by the I/O driver.

cdx6500sdlcpPacketsQueued.name: cdx6500sdlcpPacketsQueued
cdx6500sdlcpPacketsQueued.description: Total number of packets queued at the SDLC protocol layer by the transmitter.

cdx6500SPCTSDLCStationTable.name: cdx6500SPCTSDLCStationTable
cdx6500SPCTSDLCStationTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the SDLC Station table.

cdx6500SPCTSDLCStationEntry.name: cdx6500SPCTSDLCStationEntry
cdx6500SPCTSDLCStationEntry.description: A row of SDLC station configuration parameters.

cdx6500sdlcsCfgPortNum.name: cdx6500sdlcsCfgPortNum
cdx6500sdlcsCfgPortNum.description: Refers to the physical port number.

cdx6500sdlcsCfgStationNum.name: cdx6500sdlcsCfgStationNum
cdx6500sdlcsCfgStationNum.description: The number of the controller on the multidrop line. Also used for routing purposes.

cdx6500sdlcsStationAddr.name: cdx6500sdlcsStationAddr
cdx6500sdlcsStationAddr.description: The station address on the multidrop line.

cdx6500sdlcsFrameWinSize.name: cdx6500sdlcsFrameWinSize
cdx6500sdlcsFrameWinSize.description: Frame level window size must be set to the same value in devices at each end of the link.

cdx6500sdlcsAutocallMnem.name: cdx6500sdlcsAutocallMnem
cdx6500sdlcsAutocallMnem.description: This mnemonic references the remote address which will be called when polling activity is detected on the sdlc line.

cdx6500sdlcsProtocolID.name: cdx6500sdlcsProtocolID
cdx6500sdlcsProtocolID.description: The protocol identifier is the first four bytes of the call user data. If not configured the PAD will use C3000000 as the protocol ID in the call.

cdx6500sdlcsCUG.name: cdx6500sdlcsCUG
cdx6500sdlcsCUG.description: The station may be a member of up to 8 different Closed User Groups (CUGs). Each CUG membership must be a two digit number (except --)and separated by a comma. (e.g. 12,34,56,09,02,03). -- - No CUG Membership 00-99 - CUG Membership

cdx6500sdlcsOptions.name: cdx6500sdlcsOptions
cdx6500sdlcsOptions.description: Select options on this SDLC station as follows: NONE - no option specified. CUG - check closed user group in incoming calls, and insert closed user group facility in outgoing calls. QRRs - HPAD sends QRR after QLLC link comes up XIDs - TPAD responds to QXIDs with XID configured for this station XIDs are not sent to the Cluster Controller. XID3 - HPAD and TPAD will pass XIDs transparently. This option should not be set if XIDs option is selected. Corresponding station options must be XID3. RNRs - TPAD initially polls with RNR until a data packet or an QRR is received by the QLLC station on the TPAD side. DFC - the station will wait the amount of time specified by the call timer before placing the first call.

cdx6500sdlcsStationID.name: cdx6500sdlcsStationID
cdx6500sdlcsStationID.description: This is the identification sent by the TPAD in a response. to a QXID when XIDs are enabled in the QLLC Options.

cdx6500sdlcsBillingFlag.name: cdx6500sdlcsBillingFlag
cdx6500sdlcsBillingFlag.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this port. off - Billing (accounting) records will not be created for calls on this port. on - Billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this port. newvalOff - same functionality as 'off', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500sdlcsStnSubaddress.name: cdx6500sdlcsStnSubaddress
cdx6500sdlcsStnSubaddress.description: The calling subaddress is appended to the port address to create the calling address in the autocall generated.

cdx6500sdlcsGroupAddress.name: cdx6500sdlcsGroupAddress
cdx6500sdlcsGroupAddress.description: This is the address of the poll group to which this station belongs. Enter an address of 0x00 for no group membership.

cdx6500sdlcsX25Password.name: cdx6500sdlcsX25Password
cdx6500sdlcsX25Password.description: Only TPAD initiated autocall packets shall use this feature. The X.25 Network Password which may be up to 12 bytes long is inserted in the CUD of the Call Request packet. Padding with spaces must be added as necessary. Configure the Protocol ID to C3 01 00 00.

cdx6500sdlcsProtectionLevel.name: cdx6500sdlcsProtectionLevel
cdx6500sdlcsProtectionLevel.description: This specifies the level of data or connection protection which will be applied to calls to or from this port. The actual level for a call will be negotiated to the lesser of this level and the level configured for the other end of the call. none - No protection. cpOnly - Connection protection only. fullDcp - Full data and connection protection. newvalNone - same functionality as 'none', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500sdlcsReconnectTimeout.name: cdx6500sdlcsReconnectTimeout
cdx6500sdlcsReconnectTimeout.description: This specifies the number of seconds that DCP on the originating side will wait between reconnection attempts.

cdx6500sdlcsReconnectLimit.name: cdx6500sdlcsReconnectLimit
cdx6500sdlcsReconnectLimit.description: This specifies the number of times that DCP on the originating side will attempt to reconnect before clearing the call. If 0 is entered, it will not attempt to reconnect.

cdx6500sdlcsTrafficPriority.name: cdx6500sdlcsTrafficPriority
cdx6500sdlcsTrafficPriority.description: This is the traffic priority of the SDLC station; low, medium, high, or expedite. newvalLowPriority : same functionality as 'lowPriority', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500sdlcsCallTimer.name: cdx6500sdlcsCallTimer
cdx6500sdlcsCallTimer.description: This specifies the time before the next call is made. If 0 is entered, the time to the next call is handled internally. The time is in seconds.

cdx6500sdlcsIdleTimer.name: cdx6500sdlcsIdleTimer
cdx6500sdlcsIdleTimer.description: The Link Idle Timer is used by the SNA Dial on Demand feature for determining how long the station should wait for a data frame before bringing the X.25 call down. If a 0 is entered, the call will never be brought down. The time is in seconds.

cdx6500sdlcsVerConnTimer.name: cdx6500sdlcsVerConnTimer
cdx6500sdlcsVerConnTimer.description: The Verify Connection Timer is used by the SNA Dial on Demand feature for periodically verifying that the connection to the remote station is still active, after the link has been suspended. The timer specifies how long the the station waits before verifying the connection. If a 0 is entered, the connection will never be verified. The time is in seconds.

cdx6500sdlcsUnsusWaitTimer.name: cdx6500sdlcsUnsusWaitTimer
cdx6500sdlcsUnsusWaitTimer.description: The Unsuspend Wait Timer is used by the SNA Dial on Demand feature for determining how long the station will wait in LINK-UNSUSPENDING state after receiving a call request before bringing the station down. If a 0 is entered, the station waits in LINK-UNSUSPENDED state forever. Time is in seconds.

cdx6500sdlcsMaxCallAttempts.name: cdx6500sdlcsMaxCallAttempts
cdx6500sdlcsMaxCallAttempts.description: The Max Call Attempts is used to specify the number of times that the SDLC stations will attempt to autocall a remote destination. A value of zero will allow unlimited attempts.

cdx6500SPSTSDLCStationTable.name: cdx6500SPSTSDLCStationTable
cdx6500SPSTSDLCStationTable.description: All of the statistics parameters relevant to the SDLC Station table.

cdx6500SPSTSDLCStationEntry.name: cdx6500SPSTSDLCStationEntry
cdx6500SPSTSDLCStationEntry.description: A row of SDLC station Statistics parameters.

cdx6500sdlcsStatsPortNum.name: cdx6500sdlcsStatsPortNum
cdx6500sdlcsStatsPortNum.description: Refers to the physical port number.

cdx6500sdlcsQLLCState.name: cdx6500sdlcsQLLCState
cdx6500sdlcsQLLCState.description: Indicates the status of the QLLC layer: INOPERATIVE : No connection exists with the station. LINK-CLOSED : X.25 call is connected, but there has been no successful QXID exchange and data cannot pass. LINK-OPENING: The X.25 call is connected and there has been a successful QXID exchange. However, there has been no QUA or QDM response to a QSM command. LINK-OPENED : X.25 call is connected and data is passing. LINK-CLOSING: Disconnect in process. Station may come back up after an SVC clear or PVC reset. If it does not, boot the station to clear it. LINK-RECOVERY: X.25 call is connected and the station has sent a QFRMR packet over the link. Station may come back up after SVC clear or PVC reset. If it does not recover, boot the station to clear it. NOTE: This value is not supported by the 6500.

cdx6500sdlcsCharInTotal.name: cdx6500sdlcsCharInTotal
cdx6500sdlcsCharInTotal.description: Total number of characters received until now, not including SDLC header characters.

cdx6500sdlcsCharOutTotal.name: cdx6500sdlcsCharOutTotal
cdx6500sdlcsCharOutTotal.description: Total number of characters transmitted until now, not including SDLC header characters.

cdx6500sdlcsCharsInPerSec.name: cdx6500sdlcsCharsInPerSec
cdx6500sdlcsCharsInPerSec.description: The average number of characters received per second during the previous minute.

cdx6500sdlcsCharsOutPerSec.name: cdx6500sdlcsCharsOutPerSec
cdx6500sdlcsCharsOutPerSec.description: The average number of characters transmitted per second during the previous minute.

cdx6500sdlcsFramesInPerSec.name: cdx6500sdlcsFramesInPerSec

cdx6500sdlcsFramesOutPerSec.name: cdx6500sdlcsFramesOutPerSec

cdx6500sdlcsQRRInTotal.description: Total number of QRR packets received until now.

cdx6500sdlcsQRROutTotal.name: cdx6500sdlcsQRROutTotal
cdx6500sdlcsQRROutTotal.description: Total number of QRR packets transmitted until now.

cdx6500sdlcsPacketsQueued.description: Total number of packets queued at the SDLC protocol layer by the transmitter.

cdx6500sdlcsRNROutFrames.name: cdx6500sdlcsRNROutFrames
cdx6500sdlcsRNROutFrames.description: Total number of RNR frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500sdlcsSNRMInFrames.name: cdx6500sdlcsSNRMInFrames
cdx6500sdlcsSNRMInFrames.description: Total number of SNRM frames received until the present time.

cdx6500sdlcsSNRMOutFrames.name: cdx6500sdlcsSNRMOutFrames
cdx6500sdlcsSNRMOutFrames.description: Total number of SNRM frames transmitted until the present time.

cdx6500sdlcsUAInFrames.name: cdx6500sdlcsUAInFrames
cdx6500sdlcsUAInFrames.description: Total number of UA frames received until the present time.

cdx6500sdlcsUAOutFrames.name: cdx6500sdlcsUAOutFrames
